title: Drag Formula
text: Recall the drag force formula: F $$=$$ $$\frac{1}{2} C ρ A v^2$$ where C is the drag coefficient, ρ is the mass density of the fluid, and A is the reference area.

title: Find the Drag Coefficient C for Skydiver
text: Recall the drag coefficient C for a horizontal skydiver is $$1.0$$, and the density of air is $$1.21$$.

title: Plug In and Solve for the Terminal Velocity
text: Solve for v (in $$\frac{m}{s}$$, rounded to nearest whole number): $$0.56\times9.8$$ $$=$$ $$1\frac{1}{2}\times1.21\times0.0144 v^2$$.
